        "body": "## Stack Refresh\n\nRestacked on #84290 after the Doctor note policy simplification.\n\nCurrent parent: #84290 (`doctor-next-plugin-registry`).\nCurrent head is a single commit on top of that parent.\n\n## Contract Notes\n\nThis PR follows the refreshed structured Doctor contract:\n\n```ts\ndetect(ctx, scope?) -> HealthFinding[]\nrepair(ctx, findings) -> HealthRepairResult\n```\n\nFindings are machine/CI/lint signal. Human presentation uses `ctx.doctor.note(message, title?)`. Sandbox repair prompts now bridge legacy `DoctorPrompter.note(...)` calls through that sink instead of `repairNote` or deferred note arrays.\n\n## Scope\n\nConverts sandbox registry, image, and scope doctor checks to structured findings, repair results, effects, and dry-run behavior.\n\n## Verification\n\n- Restacked on refreshed #84290.\n- Confirmed by code search that this branch does not reintroduce `HealthPresentationNote`, `repairNote`, `detectionNotes`, `repairNotes`, or structured note result surfaces.\n- `git diff --check` passed during conflict resolution.\n- No focused test rerun completed in this local worktree; use fresh CI for broad proof.\r\n",
